EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to providing tenants with information regarding the senior citizens rent increase exemption and the disability rent increase exemption.
EventItemMatterName: Providing tenants with information regarding the senior citizens rent increase exemption and the disability rent increase exemption.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Education
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the Board of Trustees of the State University of New York to require a new application and public hearing when the designated community school district in a charter school application changes.
EventItemMatterName: Board of Trustees of the State University of NY to require a new application and public hearing when the designated community school district in a charter school application changes.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Finance
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to introduce and pass, and the Governor to sign, legislation establishing a property tax credit for commercial landlords who voluntarily limit the amount of rent increases to small business owner tenants upon lease renewal.
EventItemMatterName: Establishing a property tax credit for commercial landlords who voluntarily limit the amount of rent increases to small business owner tenants upon lease renewal.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on General Welfare
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring the department of homeless services to educate homeless persons on domestic violence
EventItemMatterName: Requiring the dept of homeless services to educate homeless persons on domestic violence.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Higher Education
EventItemTitle: Resolution urging the United States Department of Education and Arne Duncan, Secretary of Education, to reconsider the “Gainful Employment” rule that as proposed could derail the educational careers of millions of Americans and have a disproportionately negative effect on low-income and minority students who want to attend college.
EventItemMatterName: DOE and Arne Duncan, Secretary of Education, to reconsider the “Gainful Employment” rule.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Women's Issues
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the United States Senate to ratify the United Nations Convention on the Elimination of All Forms of Discrimination Against Women (CEDAW).
EventItemMatterName: Senate to ratify the United Nations Convention on the Elimination of All Forms of Discrimination Against Women (CEDAW).

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Women's Issues
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the United States Congress to pass legislation to protect a woman’s health, her right to determine whether and when to bear a child, and her ability to exercise that right by limiting government interference with the provision of abortion services and ensuring legal, safe abortion care is available to any woman who needs it.
EventItemMatterName: Protect a woman’s health, her right to determine whether and when to bear a child, and her ability to exercise that right by limiting government interference.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Finance
EventItemTitle: Resolution approving the new designation and changes in the designation of certain organizations to receive funding in the Expense Budget.
EventItemMatterName: Approving the new designation and changes in the designation of certain organizations to receive funding in the Expense Budget.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the curbs adjacent to a fire hydrant or bus stop.
EventItemMatterName: Curbs adjacent to a fire hydrant or bus stop.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on the New York State Legislature to pass and Governor to sign legislation requiring New York State Homes and Community Renewal to collect succession rights data from property owners and release a summary of the statistics to the public.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring NYS Homes and Community Renewal to collect succession rights data from property owners and release a summary of the statistics to the public.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Finance
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring owners of residential property with six to ten units to submit income and expense statements.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring owners of residential property with six to ten units to submit income and expense statements.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York City Rent Guidelines Board to discontinue consideration of the Price Index of Operating Costs in assessing the economic condition of the residential real estate industry to determine the annual rent adjustments for dwelling units subject to the Rent Stabilization Law.
EventItemMatterName: Rent Guidelines Board to discontinue consideration of the Price Index of Operating Costs.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Technology
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to securing personal information privacy.
EventItemMatterName: Securing personal information privacy.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Technology
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to personal information security.
EventItemMatterName: Personal information security.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Governmental Operations
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York in relation to improving young adults’ access to voter registration materials by requiring the department of education of the city of New York and the board of elections of the city of New York to provide students with registration materials in appropriate languages and to track and report on the efficacy of distributing registration materials to students.
EventItemMatterName: Improving young adults’ access to voter registration materials.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Civil Rights
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to housing accommodations and tenant black lists.
EventItemMatterName: Housing accommodations and tenant black lists.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Parks and Recreation
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the length of the season for city beaches and pools
EventItemMatterName: Length of the season for city beaches and pools.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Education
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the New York city charter, in relation to improving security in schools on election days.
EventItemMatterName: Improving security in schools on election days.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Cultural Affairs, Libraries and International Intergroup Relations
EventItemTitle: Resolution commemorating the 70th anniversary of the liberation of the Auschwitz-Birkenau concentration camps on January 27th, 2015.
EventItemMatterName: Commemorating the 70th anniversary of the liberation of the Auschwitz-Birkenau concentration camps on 1/27/15.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to prohibiting the issuance of multiple bus lane violation tickets for the same infraction within a one hour period.
EventItemMatterName: Prohibiting the issuance of multiple bus lane violation tickets for the same infraction within a one hour period.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Civil Service and Labor
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring successor employers in the grocery industry to retain eligible employees for a transitional employment period.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring successor employers in the grocery industry to retain eligible employees for a transitional employment period.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring energy efficiency reports to be filed every five years.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring energy efficiency reports to be filed every five years.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Environmental Protection
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on Governor Andrew Cuomo to veto the application by Liberty Natural Gas, LLC to construct the Port Ambrose liquefied natural gas terminal off the coast of New York.
EventItemMatterName: Governor Andrew Cuomo to veto the application by Liberty Natural Gas, LLC to construct the Port Ambrose liquefied natural gas terminal off the coast of NY.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Environmental Protection
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York Power Authority to permanently set a competitive electricity rate at the Brooklyn Cruise Terminal in order to facilitate the use of shore-based electrical power by cruise ships that wish to cease idling in the port and reduce their air pollutant emissions.
EventItemMatterName: NY Power Authority to permanently set a competitive electricity rate at the Brooklyn Cruise Terminal.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Health
EventItemTitle: Resolution to recognize “Meatless Monday” in New York City.
EventItemMatterName: Recognize “Meatless Monday” in NYC.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to suspending alternate side parking regulations on primary election day.
EventItemMatterName: Suspending alternate side parking regulations on primary election day.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Recovery and Resiliency
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on the Federal Emergency Management Agency to re-examine all National Flood Insurance Program insurance claim payouts related to Hurricane Sandy for possible underpayment, and to henceforth require insurance companies to make available to flood insurance claimants all drafts of engineering reports that are used in the assessment of damages.
EventItemMatterName: Federal Emergency Management Agency to re-examine all National Flood Insurance Program insurance claim payouts related to Hurricane Sandy for possible underpayment.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Environmental Protection
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to an annual report on drainage infrastructure.
EventItemMatterName: Annual report on drainage infrastructure.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Public Safety
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the City of New York, in relation to creating a civil penalty for any individual who is convicted of fraud or property related crimes that occur in a mandatory evacuation zone during a mandatory evacuation period.
EventItemMatterName: Creating a civil penalty for any individual who is convicted of fraud or property related crimes that occur in a mandatory evacuation zone during a mandatory evacuation period.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Technology
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to an annual report on commercial access to broadband.
EventItemMatterName: Annual report on commercial access to broadband.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to limiting the duration of street resurfacing projects.
EventItemMatterName: Limiting the duration of street resurfacing projects.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Governmental Operations
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on the New York State Legislature to pass, and the Governor to sign, A.8582-A and S.3813-B, which would allow early voting in New York State.
EventItemMatterName: Allow early voting in New York State (A.8582-A and S.3813-B)

EventItemMatterName: Criminal Justice Reform Act (CJRA) - Requiring the police department to submit quarterly reports relating to the issuance of summonses.

EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to require all New York City funded daycare centers and programs that serve forty or more children to provide an on-site social worker and to increase the per-child slot reimbursement amount.
EventItemMatterName: Require all NYC funded daycare centers and programs that serve forty or more children to provide an on-site social worker and to increase the per-child slot reimbursement amount.
